To create a Java program that reads an Excel file and exports its content to a SQL database, you will need the following libraries:

1. Apache POI for reading Excel files
2. JDBC (Java Database Connectivity) for connecting to the SQL database

First, download the required JAR files from the following links:
- [Apache POI](https://poi.apache.org/download.html)
- [JDBC Driver](https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/) (assuming you are using MySQL)

Add these JAR files to your project's classpath.

Now, let's create the Java program step by step:

Step 1: Import necessary classes
```java
import java.io.FileInputStream;
import java.sql.Connection;
import java.sql.DriverManager;
import java.sql.PreparedStatement;

import org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Cell;
import org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Row;
import org.apache.poi.xssf.usermodel.XSSFSheet;
import org.apache.poi.xssf.usermodel.XSSFWorkbook;
```

Step 2: Create a method to read data from the Excel file and insert it into the SQL database
```java
public class ExcelToDatabase {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        // Load the Excel file
        FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream("path/to/your/excel/file.xlsx");
        XSSFWorkbook workbook = new XSSFWorkbook(fis);
        XSSFSheet sheet = workbook.getSheetAt(0);

        // Connect to the SQL database
        String url = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/your_database_name";
        String user = "your_username";
        String password = "your_password";
        Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, password);

        // Iterate through each row in the Excel sheet
        for (Row row : sheet) {
            if (row.getRowNum() == 0) { // Skip header row
                continue;
            }

            // Read data from each cell in the row
            String col1 = getStringCellValue(row.getCell(0));
            String col2 = getStringCellValue(row.getCell(1));
            int col3 = (int) row.getCell(2).getNumericCellValue();

            // Insert data into the SQL database
            String sql = "INSERT INTO your_table_name (column1, column2, column3) VALUES (?, ?, ?)";
            PreparedStatement pstmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);
            pstmt.setString(1, col1);
            pstmt.setString(2, col2);
            pstmt.setInt(3, col3);
            pstmt.executeUpdate();
        }

        // Close resources
        workbook.close();
        fis.close();
        conn.close();
    }

    private static String getStringCellValue(Cell cell) {
        if (cell == null) {
            return "";
        }
        return cell.getStringCellValue();
    }
}
```

Replace `path/to/your/excel/file.xlsx`, `your_database_name`, `your_username`, `your_password`, and table/column names with appropriate values.

Now you can run this Java program to read an Excel file and export its content to a SQL database.

